node.text:
The full story and photoseries of my last 2 months in Kyrgyzstan is now online on my website. Here are 10 images from the series, the full series has over 30 photos. For this trip I mainly explored the border areas in the south with China, Kyzyl Asker and also visited the Khan Tengri Basecamp. All in all it was great to be in nature for a longer period of time again after spending most of the year at home.
.

Lots of people always ask me how I edit my images. I have a full extensive course available on that with new content only this week because of the heather season. Check my stories for details.

This first image is one I found in my archives from 2016. I never edited this shot before and also included it as a new lecture in the course. Happy learning and shooting this season!
.

I have so many images of the blooming heather in the Netherlands in my archives. I started photographing it many years ago. Back then it was not popular at all. Most of the images in this series are from previous years, but there is one that I took only a few days ago. Can you guess which one is new?

node.text:
A small series of changing light on peak Dankova. Close to 6000m, 5982 to be precise. This peak is located in a remote are of Kyrgyzstan close to the border of China. The sunset with no clouds didn't make the light less spectacular as we witnessed very deep colours changing from orange, yellow to deep blues and purples during twilight. After that the full moon rose and Mr and my friends of #visitkarakol had to drive fast on bumpy roads to be able to frame it just above the peak. As always, the moon shot was planned with #photopills.
.
#kyrgyzstan #mountainlove #mountainadventures #mountainview #mountainpeak #moonlight #moonrise #fullmoon #sonyalpha #madewithluminar  #remoteplaces #kyrgyzstantravel

node.text:
It's hard to imagine going from Khan Tengri BC with freezing cold nights back to Bishkek with close to 40 degrees. These 2 images I took on the morning of my helicopter flight back. After another night of frost I decided to check out the little puddles before the Heli arrived and was not disappointed. It's very difficult to find foregrounds in this area as it's basically only rocks and stones. So having some cool frozen puddles was nice to leave with.
.
On the first photo you see the giant Peak Pobeda that's over 7400m on the left, lit by the sun (along with the entire range). It was a great experience hanging around here for a few days (with @aksaitravel.kg ) . Basically all the people we saw there and spoke to were climbers. Not only the scenery was great, but it was also great to learn the climbers culture. I have extreme respect for those people, basically risking their life climbing these 7000+ giants like Khan Tengri and Peak Pobeda. Climbing in Kyrgyzstan has a certain danger to it as there is almost no possibility of rescue because of no resources.
.
If there are any climbers following me I'm definitely interested in hearing your stories on climbing in Kyrgyzstan
.
#mountainadventures #aksaitravel #visitkarakol #kyrgyzrepublic #kyrgyzstan #mountainview #mountainlove #mountainlovers #peakpobeda #tianshan #kyrgyzstan_trip #kyrgyzstantravel #amazingplaces #sonyalpha #madewithluminar

node.text:
I just got back from Khan Tengri Basecamp but before I have time to show you images from the last few days I still have lots of work from my earlier trip about a week ago to the remote south of Kyrgyzstan close to the border with China.
.
You can see Kyzyl Asker (5832m) in all of these photos. In the first photo we found an area with an endless sea of flowers. It was very interesting to see how they grow on basically just stones. We found all kinds of interesting foregrounds in this area, even a skull of a Marco Polo sheep.
.
Kyrgyzstan has neverending possibilities of adventures and I'm happy to explore them always with my good friends of #visitkarakol
.
#kyrgyzstan #mountainlove #mountainadventures #mountainview #mountainlovers #flowerpower #nomadlife #kyrgyzstantravel #sonyalpha #madewithluminar #amazingplaces

A couple of days ago I found myself in an area named Kok-Kiya Valley. The backdrop of mountains lit up by the last sun light and the swirling rivers lined up for a drone shot. These rivers reminded me from my adventures from Iceland. 
.

node.text:
It's almost august again. Every year I love photographing the dreamy purple heather in the Netherlands. Foggy mornings with the purple flowers and the nice trees make up for a fairytale scenery. I hope I can photograph it this year as I am currently still in Kyrgyzstan. 
.
